         <!-- See spear/818 -->
         <div type="work" xml:id="work-26" n="26">
            <div type="section" xml:id="section-26">
               <head type="main">Next the Twenty-Sixth History, of the Holy <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2125">Thomas</persName> the Persecuted Man and
                  Martyr, Bishop of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/66">Damascus</placeName>.</head>
               <ab xml:id="section-26.1" n="1"> Whereas we have though enigmatically and obscurely set
                  down a nar<pb type="vol" n="541"/><pb type="running" rend="brackets" n="339"/>rative concerning the divine dispensation
                  through these two brave warriors and true pastors <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/74">John</persName> and <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/50">John</persName>, we must after the same
                  pattern introduce into the series that is connected with them this third saint
                  also, <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2125">Thomas</persName> the bishop,
                  the whole of whose keen enthusiasm and active administration in God's church is
                  the same as theirs. For, as the holy....<ptr type="noteAnchor" xml:id="a1" target="#n1" n="1"/>
               </ab>
            </div>
         </div>
         <noteGrp>
            <note xml:id="n1" target="#a1" n="1">
               <choice>
                  <reg/>
                  <orig>p. 339, n. 1</orig>
               </choice>The rest of the chapter is lost.</note>
         </noteGrp>
